direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods provide iteration over the list, with listIterator offering more functionalities like adding and removing elements during iteration.
Similar to iterator(), listIterator(int) also provides iteration over the list starting from a specified index, offering additional functionalities.
Both methods access elements within the list, though get(int) directly retrieves an element by index while iterator() provides sequential access.
Both methods involve searching for elements within the list, though indexOf(Object) searches for a specific object and returns its index.
Both methods involve operations on elements within the list, though remove(int) directly removes an element by index.
Both methods involve operations on elements within the list, though set(int, E) directly sets an element at a specified index.
Both methods involve accessing elements within the list, though toArray() converts the entire list into an array.
